cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on developing a deep learning approach for estimating accurate 3D geometry of transparent objects for robotic manipulation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as deep convolutional networks to infer surface normals and masks of transparent surfaces, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic datasets and real-world test benchmarks, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with grasping algorithms, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics).
